26/10/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The government examined a justice ministry briefing on the National Anti-Corruption Strategy on Friday (24 October).
Documents focused on measures in several specific areas, such as privatisation, the health sector and justice.
Another part of the document dealt with measures proposed to ensure staff integrity.
On Saturday, Romania honoured its army.
President Ion Iliescu congratulated military on efforts at home and abroad, especially in Iraq and Afghanistan.
(Rompres - 25/10/03)
